\ls1\ilvl0
\b0 \cf3 {\listtext	\'95	}2 \'bc cups raw unsalted cashews\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 T. canola oil or olive oil\
{\listtext	\'95	}\'bd T. fresh orange juice or lemon juice\
{\listtext	\'95	}\'bc t. salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}\'bd t. - 1 t. agave nectar (optional)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\sa360\ql\qnatural

\b \cf3 Preparation:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\sa360\ql\qnatural

\b0 \cf3 1. In a food processor, process the cashews until they resemble a very fine, almost powdery, meal. Add the oil, fresh orange juice and salt, and blend for 30 seconds to 1 minute. Using a rubber spatula, scrape down the sides of the blender, making sure that the mixture is consistent and no clumps remain in the bottom. Blend for 30 seconds more. Test the cashew butter, adding agave nectar or more oil or salt as desired. Transfer to an airtight container and refrigerate.\
